          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "EDEG",
                "GSPEC",
                "MOSEP",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Enriched Zn",
                "targets were prepared by electro-deposition onto Ni",
                "backing. Cu targets were cut as 10 mm diam. The",
                "proton and alpha particle irradiations were done at",
                "the AVF-930 isochronous cyclotron of NIRS, Chiba. The",
                "primary energies were 39.96 MeV with alpha particles",
                "and 29.86 MeV with protons. In the case of the alpha",
                "experiments 10 and 7 samples, respectively, were",
                "activated together with 20 and 30 micron thick Ti",
                "foils. For the 68Zn + p study, Cu (thickness: 9",
                "micron) and Au (thickness: 50 micron) foils were used",
                "as monitors and degraders, respectively. Irradiation",
                "time: 1 hour. Beam intensity: 50 and 100 nA for alpha",
                "beam and 50nA for proton beam."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Charges obtained by the current integrator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "EN-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "The uncertainty in the primary beam energy was",
                "estimated to be +-0.30  MeV (for alpha particles) and",
                "+-0.25 MeV (for protons) but due to the straggling",
                "effect and foil thickness uncertainties it increases",
                "gradually along the stack  and reaches +-1.1 and",
                "+-0.8MeV, respectively, at the end of the stacks."
              ]
            },
